    {
        "sha": "00000006fadc4550c696939966d63157024ab63b",
        "author": "masklinn",
        "email": "github.com@masklinn.net",
        "date": "2023-11-15T16:18:10Z",
        "message": "Add support for a help flag\n\nWhile lucky-commit has a pretty simple interface, because it operates\nby side-effects it can be safer to check its behaviour.\n\nCurrently, to get the help it's necessary to be lucky enough to\nmistakenly give it 2 args, thus failing to match any case. Otherwise,\nit will panic if called from not-within-a-repository, and silently\nrewrite the HEAD if invoked from one.",
        "url": "https://github.com/not-an-aardvark/lucky-commit/commit/00000006fadc4550c696939966d63157024ab63b"
    },
